  "prompt": "What's the difference between attitude and character?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of the key differences between attitude and character:\n\nAttitude:\n1. More situational and changeable\n2. Reflects current emotions and perspective\n3. Can be influenced by mood and immediate circumstances\n4. How you respond to specific situations\n5. More external and observable\n6. Can shift relatively quickly\n\nCharacter:\n1. More deeply rooted and stable\n2. Reflects core values, principles, and moral standards\n3. Developed over time through experiences and choices\n4. Represents fundamental traits and behaviors\n5. More internal and consistent\n6. Changes very slowly, if at all\n\nExample:\n- Attitude: Being grumpy one day because you're tired\n- Character: Consistently showing kindness and integrity regardless of circumstances\n\nWhile attitude can fluctuate, character represents a person's fundamental essence and tends to remain more consistent over time. Attitude is like the weather (changeable), while character is like the climate (more enduring).\n\nYour attitude might vary day to day, but your character defines who you are at your core.",
